    <worksheet name='Conversion by Journey Length'>
      <layout-options>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run>The trends of User Conversion Rate and Distinct Users for Journey Length.  Color shows details about User Conversion Rate and Distinct Users.
</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Observed user conversion rate (user-level) and distinct users (n) by journey length</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> (touchpoints per user).
Color indicates conversion rate.
Interpretation: conversion rises early then gains diminish; long journeys have smaller n. </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Descriptive only (no causality).</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
        <view>
